## 5. Install the Chef DK on your Ubuntu instance

Remember, for learning purposes, you'll start by managing a server directly. To do that, you'll install the Chef DK on your virtual machine. The Chef DK provides tools that enable you to manage your servers remotely from your workstation. But it also provides tools that allow you to configure a machine directly.

From your SSH connection, first update the `apt` cache and then install `curl`.

```bash
# ~
$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get -y install curl
```

Next, run this to install the Chef DK.

<% command_snippet(path: 'learn-the-basics/ubuntu/gcp/set-up-your-own-server/install-the-chef-dk/install-chefdk', workstation: 'ubuntu', features: [:stdin, :stderr, :stdout]) %>

The `-c` and `-v` arguments specify the Chef DK version this module was last tested with.

